 as both a normal turbojet for speeds up to Mach 2, and switches to Turbo R=
amjet for speeds up to Mach 3.3. It&#8217;s very expensive and inefficient,=
 but very fast.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Rockets are the most extr=
eme version of the trade-off. They have to carry all of their own fuel and =
oxidizer (essentially liquid air) to create the combustion reaction that ma=
kes the exhaust that pushes out the back of the rocket to propel it upwards=
=2E Carrying everything it needs for th=
e whole journey instead of using the e=
arth&#8217;s free air makes it super inefficient in earth&#8217;s atmospher=
e at low speeds, but rockets are the only way to fly in space, and the only=
 way to go very fast, like orbital velocity at Mach 25. It&#8217;s super in=
efficient and expensive, but the only choice at those speeds and altitudes.=
