style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Astro Mechanica isn&#8217;t a SpaceX competitor, but i=
t </span><em>does</em><span> want to take over Boeing&#8217;s place at the =
head of airplane manufacturing.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, =
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">You don&#=
8217;t beat Boeing at its own game, even in Boeing&#8217;s current form. Bo=
eing, and its one competitor, Airbus, benefit from scale economies, high sw=
itching costs, and cornered resources in the form of contracts and congress=
men. Building a 787 competitor and trying to sell it to airlines would be a=
n incredibly expensive fool&#8217;s errand.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>So i=
nstead, Astro Mechanica plans to start at the high end of the market by bui=
lding </span><strong>small supersonic private planes</strong><span> (Supers=
onic Transports, in industry parlance, or SST)&#160; and selling them to cu=
stomers for whom time is (a lot of) money.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">I&#8217;m oversimplifying, but Astro Mechanica can essentially pull the r=
ocket out of the launch system and replace it with some leather seats and a=
 bathroom to carry humans across the earth instead of satellites to outer s=
pace.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static" style=3D"fon=
