ght: 1.16em; margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>The Wrig=
ht Stuff</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Ian Brooke grew up in rural Califor=
nia among the Redwoods, where he learned physics by racing around the redwo=
ods.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;If you grow up in the city, you lear=
n human rules. They&#8217;re made up rules. They&#8217;re not real,&#8221; =
he told me. &#8220;We built jumps with tractors and raced through trees, an=
d when you fall from one of those, the fall is real. Building up that intui=
tion is a useful skill to have.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, =
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">From a ve=
ry young age, Ian wanted to fly fighter jets, but from a very young age, he=
 knew that it wouldn&#8217;t be on his terms, and that he probably wouldn&#=
8217;t qualify for the job anyways. If he made the fighter plane, though, n=
o one could stop him from flying it. That became the goal.&#160;</p><p styl=
e=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 20px 0;"><span>The way that Ian laid his path, intentionally or not, seem=
s to have been to </span><strong>work on smaller models of things and then =
use the intuition earned to make bigger and bigger things.&#160;</strong></=
p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;">He built model airplanes and became a pilot, learning h=
ow planes fit together, and how they feel to fly. &#8220;I have some pilot =
friends,&#8221; he said, &#8220;who could never explain how or why the plan=
e does the thing, but they have a good built-in model for how things move t=
hrough the world.&#8221;&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-=
size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Ian wanted to do =
both &#8211; to understand and feel, to be a builder and operator. &#8220;I=
 want to build better things to operate.&#8221; He wanted to become a </spa=
n><strong>full-stack engineer</strong><span>.</span></p><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><=
span>He also became a </span><strong>full-stack entrepreneur</strong><span>=
=2E&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Before Astro Mechanica, Ian ran a succe=
ssful bootstrapped motorcycle company. He made things, handled sales, took =
customer support calls, and did the books. He designed the thing, machined =
the thing, and sold the thing. There aren&#8217;t many people who do all th=
ree.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Proof came randomly when I was talkin=
g to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/b4390c5e-ae2b-4737-a76=
6-ed427c4f74b5?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">M=
att Parlmer</a><span>, the founder of Not Boring Capital portfolio company =
</span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/44c2f752-f59b-4378-bbff-fbe=
152842cac?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNp=
U" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">Genera=
l Fabrication</a><span>, a couple weeks ago. General Fabrication makes mach=
ines that can make anything, starting with 3D printers that make plastic pa=
rts. As we were talking through potential customers, about companies full o=
f strong engineers that Matt expects to land, I brought up Astro Mechanica.=
&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;That one&#8217;s unlikely,&#8221;=
 Matt told me. &#8220;Ian built motorcycles by hand. That dude can machine =
anything himself.&#8221; That&#8217;s absurdly high praise coming from Matt=
=2E&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=20=
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Anyway, while Ian was making motorcycles, his =
mind was always on the skies. Back in 2019, he started to think through how=
 you&#8217;d design an engine that would make flying private as cheap as ai=
rliners.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>He knew it was possible. </span><=
strong>Private jets take 20-30,000 man hours to assemble, which is crazy, b=
ecause a car, which is more mechanically complicated, takes 40-50.&#160;</s=
trong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>(I like this way of thinking. Valar Atomi=
cs CEO Isaiah Taylor made a similar point about </span><a href=3D"https://s=
ubstack.com/redirect/fdd4d8e8-f1bc-4772-b3f5-ab33d193656c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ=
