54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">nuclear reactor construction on A=
ge of Miracles</a><span>. Elon Musk has a related concept: the Idiot Index)=
=2E&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: r=
gb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;What fact of engineering require=
s that it takes an entire human life to manufacture a private jet?&#8221; h=
e asked when we first spoke.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Spoiler: there isn&=
#8217;t one. It was just really complex, and hard for anyone to hold everyt=
hing it would take to make one in their head.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Ian thou=
ght he could. By starting with very small things, like model airplanes, and=
 moving up to bigger things, like experimental airplanes, he had a sixth se=
nse for how things fit together, and for what it takes to maintain them whe=
n they fall apart.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>On </span><em>First Pri=
nciples</em><span>, he told Christian, &#8220;I just know that if you put t=
his thing there, it&#8217;s going to be miserable to assemble and expensive=
 to fix. Imagine you have a bunch of planes out there. How does the mechani=
c interact with it when it comes in for maintenance? You have to think abou=
t the Mechanic Experience.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If that=
 seems like skipping a few steps ahead when Astro Mechanica hasn&#8217;t bu=
ilt a single aircraft yet, that&#8217;s the point as Ian sees it.&#160;</p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">&#8220;Most engineers don&#8217;t understand what&#8217;s=
 involved in actually making the thing they come up with,&#8221; he told me=
=2E &#8220;My secret sauce is that I&#8=
217;ve spent my life becoming the pers=
on who builds the thing. I&#8217;m a pilot first and foremost, I know why t=
hings are engineered the way they are, and I know the manufacturing process=
=2E There&#8217;s always some trade-off=
