le=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">There are three pillars of the business: Engines, Airframes, an=
d Operations.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">To date, they&#8217;ve built the c=
ore of the Engine team, because without the engine, nothing else matters. T=
his core &#8211; the Space Mongols &#8211; will make the next set of hires,=
 which will make the next, and so on out from there.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">Next, Ian is replicating the Engine team&#8217;s structure to build ou=
t the Airframes team, which will build the airplanes that the Engine team w=
ill bolt its baby onto. This team should be about 12 people to get to a wor=
king airframe.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Then, they&#8217;ll replicate the=
 org structure again to hire an Operations team, which will work with regul=
ators, partners, and customers to get the engines and airframes into the sk=
y.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Each one of these core teams will be the foun=
dation for much bigger organizations along those same three lines as the co=
mpany grows. If they get the foundation just right, Ian thinks it should be=
 able to scale up.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There&#8217;s a clear paralle=
l between the way Ian designs physical things and the way he designs teams:=
 start with the small model, understand it inside and out, understand how e=
ach piece trades off with the others, and only when you have a full intuiti=
on of the thing: scale it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">One of the bets on As=
tro Mechanica is that the same pattern holds for organizations, or that Ian=
 will be able to adapt if it doesn&#8217;t.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But =
that&#8217;s a future problem, one that he&#8217;ll have to earn the right =
to solve. First, they need to prove that this Turboelectric Adaptive Engine=
 does what they think it can.&#160;</p><h4 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widg=
et" style=3D"-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: =
