e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>The company has had =
as smooth a path as possible to this point in the journey, particularly for=
 a company that&#8217;s </span><em>building a new kind of jet engine</em><s=
pan>. I would imagine that VCs are going to be all over it after demo day (=
and that many are trying to get ahead of that rush as we speak).&#160;</spa=
n></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26p=
x; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">VC funding isn&#8217;t a goal; it&#8217;s a destina=
tion. But in the case of this business, so much will depend on its ability =
to find financial partners who support its more-for-more vision of aerospac=
e that financing is as core to the business as the engine itself.&#160;</p>=
<p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 20px 0;">Cash is its fuel, and whether it crashes, simply sells a =
better engine, builds a nice launch business, or takes the baton from Boein=
g and drags aerospace into the Turboelectric Age will depend in large part =
on how it balances its own speed and efficiency from here.&#160;</p><h3 cla=
ss=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-appearance: optimizelegibili=
ty; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -webkit-appearance: optimizelegib=
ility; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; appearance: optimizelegibility;=
 color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-family: 'SF Pro Display', -apple-system-headl=
ine, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helv=
etica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI =
Symbol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin=
: 1em 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>Pursuing Moonshots&#160;</s=
trong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Financialization couldn&#8217;t save Boeing, o=
r the airline industry as we know it. </p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Trying to get m=
ore-for-less without technological progress &#8211; more revenue on fewer a=
ssets by outsourcing, more seats in the same plane by shrinking seats &#821=
1; is a one-way ticket to stagnation and decline.&#160;&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">I&#8217;ve argued that it&#8217;s not Boeing&#8217;s fault, or an=
y of the airlines&#8217; fault, but a natural consequence of reaching the e=
nd of a technological paradigm that&#8217;s had so much juice squeezed out =
of it already. It was inevitable.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Astro Me=
chanica wants to get more-for-less the right way: through technology. </spa=
n><strong>More speed for less cost through adaptive engines. </strong><span=
>That engine is just the start.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, =
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Astro Mec=
hanica plans to:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li styl=
e=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-siz=
ing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><span>Build a new kind o=
f engine: the </span><strong>Turboelectric Adaptive Engine</strong><span>&#=
160;</span></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: =
bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4p=
x;"><span>Use it to </span><strong>launch rockets</strong></p></li><li styl=
e=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-siz=
ing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><span>Use the cash and d=
ata from the rockets to build </span><strong>small private supersonic plane=
s</strong></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: b=
ullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px=
;"><span>Use the cash and data from the private planes to build </span><str=
ong>commercial airliners</strong></p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>It w=
ants its </span><strong>rockets to fly 1x per week</strong><span> and its <=
/span><strong>private planes to fly 100x per week</strong><span>. To have a=
 rebuild-the-airline-industry impact, its </span><strong>commercial planes =
will one day have to fly thousands of times per week</strong><span>.&#160;<=
/span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>There&#8217;s nothing inherently defensib=
le about an engine design. </span><strong>The defensibility in this busines=
s comes from getting to scale quickly, and from building a unique business =
around the engine before anyone else does.</strong><span> Against incumbent=
s, it&#8217;s counter-positioned, which buys it time to scale, and against =
potential new entrants, it has a head start, a strong team, and the whole m=
aster plan, down to the finest detail, in Andrew&#8217;s head.&#160;</span>=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In either case, it will need to get big as fast as it=
 can. Turning out hundreds of aircraft orders of magnitude faster than they=
&#8217;re assembled today will require manufacturing prowess on par with a =
Tesla Gigafactory, and like Tesla, it will require boatloads of cash.&#160;=
</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px;=
 margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That&#8217;s OK. That&#8217;s good. We should give ou=
r most ambitious projects the most money. We should give them more so that =
they can give us back more, for less.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 5=
5, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Astr=
o Mechanica is a </span><strong><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/1b=
3eb3bc-9d95-433e-94d7-1366fde5a048?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaM=
ZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decor=
ation: underline;">Techno-Industrial</a></strong><span>. It&#8217;s using n=
ew technology to build better atoms-based products at a lower cost than was=
 previously possible.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Instead of simply s=
elling cheaper products into the existing web of mediocrity that is the air=
line industry, Astro Mechanica wants to rebuild the whole thing. Of course =
that&#8217;s going to take cash.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">I think we&#821=
7;re all scarred from the more-for-less era into believing that costs don&#=
8217;t shrink, that legacy industries don&#8217;t get rebuilt, that change =
only comes at the margins.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But what fact of engi=
neering requires that the way it&#8217;s been done is the only way it can b=
e done?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Boeing won the Jet Age by harnessing a n=
ew technology to reshape an industry, and it improved the way billions of p=
assengers travel in the process. That it&#8217;s stagnating now doesn&#8217=
;t mean that air travel is doomed to decay, but that it&#8217;s time for a =
new Age.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Boeing dominated through the peri=
od that Tyler Cowen calls </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redire=
ct/bafa59d3-b109-406b-920b-296a359f15c3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-=
decoration: underline;">The Great Stagnation</a></em><span>, a half-century=
 on a technological plateau defined by many of the evils that ate at airlin=
es.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The Great Stagnation is ending. You c=
an feel it.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; l=
ine-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">SpaceX launches multiple rockets a w=
eek. Solar is getting very cheap. EVs are overtaking gas-powered cars. Ozem=
pic is helping millions lose weight.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55=
, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Maybe Astro=
 Mechanica will bring affordable supersonic travel to humankind.&#160;</p><=
p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; marg=
in: 0 0 20px 0;">It&#8217;s going to take a ton of work, time, capital, luc=
k, skill, and adaptability. It will take getting the core of each piece of =
the business right, and then growing fractally out from there while maintai=
ning fidelity with the original thing. It will take becoming great at thing=
s that the company has never done.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If it really =
has a more-for-less engine, there are a million ways for Astro Mechanica to=
 make high-margin revenue in the short-term that require a lot less work, t=
ime, capital, luck, skill, and adaptability than this crazy plan to build T=
he Aerospace Company over decades.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, =
55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But if =
Astro Mechanica </span><em>really</em><span> has a more-for-less engine, </=
span><strong>it must pursue the moonshot</strong><span>. I want to live in =
a world that supports that pursuit.</span></p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px=
; line-height: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; heigh=
t: 1px; margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"></div><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Thanks t=
o Ian for letting me tell the Astro Mechanica story, to Christian for input=
 and feedback, and to </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/55572=
